      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>The Commission on Organization of the Executive Branch of the Government, informally referred to as the Hoover Commission 
	  because Herbert Hoover was its chairman, was appointed by President Harry S. Truman to recommend administrative changes to 
	  the federal government.</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">Hoover Commission Records</emph> contains correspondence, reports, research notes and other material.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      
      <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a">
         <head>Arrangement of the Collection</head>
         <p>The collection has received minimal processing.  Materials are in roughly alphabetical order by department (agriculture, commerce, etc.).</p>
      </arrangement>
      
